VMalolakannan and RanganathanAmutham MusicKovil ThiruvaimozhiSri NammazhwarA M 5046 - C.D.Spiritual (Rs. 99).The 12 Azhwars in the pantheon of Vaishnavism have propagated their message in Tamil, which is collectively known as the `Naalaayira Divya Prabhandham,' `Arulicheyal,' `Araiyar... . Sevai' and `Dravida Vedam.'The hymns of God realised saints, arise from the depths of their souls and are outpourings, which in communion with the Lord find ecstatic, exquisite expression in Tamil. They glorify the auspicious attributes of the Almighty.The doyen of Azhwars, Nammazhwar, has spelt out the Hindu regimen in the areas of art, literature, philosophy and religion.In this C.D. volume the Thiruppallandu, Kanninum Siruthampu and Kovil Thiruvaimozhi composed by Sri Nammazhwar, have been recited by vidwans Malolakannan and Ranganathan with great involvement and religious fervour.Extolling Shirdi SaiAnother C.D. release of Amutham Music featuring the Priya Sisters is titled Pavitra Sai, extolling Sai Baba, the saint of Shirdi. The programme comprises Sai Sahasranamam by Narasimha Swamiji, Sadasatswaroopam and Sri Mahima Stotram by Sri Upasini Baba, an Abhang by Dasganu Maharaj, Namaskarashtakam by Mohini Raj, traditional hymns, and Madhav Adkari's `Jayajaya Deva' and Arati. The oral expression by the sisters is governed by sweet melody and lyrical quality that establish an instant connection with the devotee.S.P.New releaseRanjanas Audio of Madurai (0452-2640955) has released Sri Dakshinamurthi, an album (CD and cassette) songs on Guru rendered by a team that includes Unnikrishnan. Krithiya's lyrics have been set to tune by Surriya. Price Rs. 75.S.P.Bottom Template Starts
